snippet.textDisplay:
"take her milk that's intended for her calf..." As a rancher, This guy couldn't possibly be more full of cow pie. Dairy cows produce between 6-8 gallons of milk per day. Calves are only capable of drinking maybe 1-2 gallons a day, more as it gets older. If we as ranchers don't take the remaining milk, she'll either develop a severe case of mastitis, which can potentially kill her, or she'll naturally significantly reduce the amount of milk she produces, which means the calf, as it gets older and requires more milk will not get enough to sustain it's life.  

God created these wonderful beasts that they may have glory in providing for our families. And to deny this is to deny their gift to mankind. Do you wonder why you don't see cows in the wild, sir? It's because they depend on humans to exist. They need us as much as we need them. Jackass.
